obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5337  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Double labeling of hippocampal neurons cultured for ~4 weeks with antibodies against Dasm1 and glutamate receptor 2/4 (GluR2/4) revealed a partial overlap between Dasm1 and GluR2/4 in a punctate pattern along the dendrites, especially at spine-like structures (Fig. 1A, arrowheads), suggesting that Dasm1 is localized at the excitatory synapses in mature neurons.\n\nFurthermore, subcellular fractionation of adult rat brains showed that Dasm1 was abundant in the PSD, in which postsynaptic proteins such as PSD-95 and NR2B were enriched (Fig. 1B).\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Rat brain subcellular fractionation was performed according to ...\"\n\nthe Dasm1 antibody source or generation was not described" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5337" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

